f̶̑i̸̓̄m̸͌s̸̍͝ḩ̸̎e̴̍̏ 🦖 2024-02-09 2:45 AM
well, the pelagic landscape is literally just water, and LOTS of it
2:45 AM
the only variance, being the amount of a species present in an area, and their migration routes
2:46 AM
so therefore, it is more convenient that both sexes can survive comfortably on their own, or act similarly to their school
2:47 AM
so, there's barely any reason to be different
2:47 AM
benthic fish on the other hand, are literally just domestic
2:48 AM
they settle in niches, and stick to one area that suits them best-- therefore, they have more freedom to have a dynamic relationship between male and female
2:49 AM
benthic fish are also typically the ones who have the ability to change sex
2:49 AM
since roles are connected to sex, they may switch between each, depending on the lack of another
2:50 AM
pelagic fish, having more space and more straightforward lifestyles, can exist in bulk, and therefore do not have as much of a loss
